{"TopicId":171410,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Changing root part in flight - Without KIS/KAS","CreatedByName":"MaximumThrust","CreatedById":185090,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-26T06:41:52Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"MaximumThrust","CreatedById":185090,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-26T06:41:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Real Plume mod it\u0027s a must for me, but it has a small bug: it don\u0027t work if the engine is a root part. I try to avoid this, but sometimes when decoupling the root simple goes to the engine.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIs there an easy way to change the root part in-flight? The problem is more frequently with unmanned relays clusters (a lot of parts and engines), so \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E it\u0027s not an option. Sometimes I use the cheat menu,\u00A0put a copy of the ship in place and recovery the founds, put I wanted a better way.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sarbian","CreatedById":57146,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-26T12:54:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nuh, can you describe what is happening when the engine is the root ? No fx at all ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-26T14:41:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only other way to change the root part in-flight that I know of is docking/undocking.\u00A0 Which *may* change the root part, but you won\u0027t have control over if or how it does so.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MaximumThrust","CreatedById":185090,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-26T15:15:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223305175\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171410\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519649673\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257146\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sarbian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, sarbian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nuh, can you describe what is happening when the engine is the root ? No fx at all ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, but it still work (provide thrust).\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt\u0027s a know issue:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222376238\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130576\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453586691\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232999\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nhawks17\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/23/2016 at 8:04 PM, Nhawks17 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#0000CD;\u0022\u003EKnown Issues:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nThrust limiting on engines get\u00A0reset upon install. \u003Cstrong\u003EBEWARE IN THE KSP TUTORIALS\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSwitching to a vessel with an engine as a root part will cause the plume to not show.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSmoke effects looks strange, will fix eventually.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sarbian","CreatedById":57146,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-26T15:18:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223305288\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171410\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519658134\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022185090\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MaximumThrust\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, MaximumThrust said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a know issue\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, but it is most likely a problem in SmokeScreen and it is my code.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}